HEADWORD: Supratrochlear
<hw>Su`pra*troch"le*ar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Situated over or above a trochlea or trochlear
surface; -- applied esp. to one of the subdivisions of the trigeminal
nerve.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supravaginal</ent>⟦br⟧
